<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1440,611,1083]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
Guianas, 
<collectingCountry box="[309,578,771,795]" name="British Virgin Islands" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">British Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
(Guana Island), Hispaniola, 
<collectingCountry box="[931,1038,771,795]" name="Jamaica" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
, Lesser Antilles, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1298,1440,771,795]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
(including key Caja de Muerto and Mona Island).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1440,611,1083]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
It is common to observe 
<taxonomicName box="[528,687,835,859]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decolorata">
<emphasis box="[528,687,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. decolorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in sandy areas along coasts, where females nest and males are involved in perching (
<bibRefCitation author="Torres, J. A. &amp; R. R. Snelling" box="[446,747,867,891]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="87 - 102" refId="ref16409" refString="Torres, J. A., and R. R. Snelling. 1992. Los himenopteros de Isla de Mona. Acta Cientifica 6: 87 - 102." type="journal article" year="1992">Torres and Snelling 1992</bibRefCitation>
; personal observations of authors; see 
<figureCitation box="[1197,1280,867,891]" captionStart="Figure 16-29" captionStartId="10.[192,276,1813,1835]" captionTargetBox="[207,1426,192,1791]" captionTargetId="figure-22@10.[202,1426,192,1792]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 16-29. Apidae. 16) Anthophora tricolor (Fabr.). 17) Centris smithii Cresson. 18) C. decolorata Lepeletier. 19) C. lanipes (Fabr.). 20) C. haemorrhoidalis (Fabr.). 21) Exomalopsis analis Spinola. 22) Exomalopsis bahamica Timberlake. 23) Melissodes trifasciata Cresson. 24) Nomada pilipes (Cresson). 25) N. krugii Cresson. 26) Xeromelecta tibialis (Fabr.). 27) Mesoplia rufipes (Perty). 28-29) Xylocopa mordax F. Smith." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169674" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169674/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). The MEBT- MC and UPRM collections contain specimens of this species identified by K. V. Krombein as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis box="[1292,1440,899,923]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. versicolor</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wolcott, G. N." box="[337,505,931,955]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="5 - 313" refId="ref16624" refString="Wolcott, G. N. 1923. &quot; Insectae Portoricensis &quot;. A preliminary annotated checklist of the insects of Porto Rico, with descriptions of some new species. Journal of the Department of Agriculture of Puerto Rico 7: 5 - 313." type="journal article" year="1923">
<taxonomicName authority="Genaro &amp; Franz, 2008" authorityName="Genaro &amp; Franz" authorityYear="2008" box="[337,430,931,955]" genus="Wolcott" pageId="12" pageNumber="24" rank="genus" status="G. N.">Wolcott</taxonomicName>
(1923
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wolcott, G. N." box="[515,576,931,955]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 600" refId="ref16670" refString="Wolcott, G. N. 1936. &quot; Insectae Borinquenses &quot;. A revised annotated check-list of the insects of Puerto Rico. Journal of the Department of Agriculture of Puerto Rico 20: 1 - 600." type="journal article" year="1936">1936</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wolcott, G. N." box="[587,646,931,955]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="749 - 975" refId="ref16709" refString="Wolcott, G. N. 1948. The insects of Puerto Rico. Hymenoptera. Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico 32: 749 - 975." type="journal article" year="1948">1948</bibRefCitation>
) erroneously reported this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1122,1262,931,955]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Torres, J. A. &amp; R. R. Snelling" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="87 - 102" refId="ref16409" refString="Torres, J. A., and R. R. Snelling. 1992. Los himenopteros de Isla de Mona. Acta Cientifica 6: 87 - 102." type="journal article" year="1992">Torres and Snelling 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Additional misidentifications of this kind appear in 
<bibRefCitation author="Dewitz, H." box="[1036,1212,963,987]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="197 - 208" refId="ref12110" refString="Dewitz, H. 1881. Hymenopteren von Portorico. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift 25: 197 - 208." type="journal article" year="1881">Dewitz (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stahl, A." box="[1225,1381,963,987]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" refId="ref16208" refString="Stahl, A. 1882. Catalogo del gabinete zoologico del Dr A. Stahl, precedido de una clasificacion sistematica de los animales que corresponden a esta fauna. Imprenta del Boletin Mercantil; San Juan. 248 p." type="book" year="1882">Ståhl (1882)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado Capriles, J. &amp; C. A. Navarro" box="[192,680,995,1019]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="45 - 64" refId="ref14381" refString="Maldonado Capriles, J., and C. A. Navarro. 1967. Additions and corrections to Wolcott's &quot; Insects of Puerto Rico &quot;. Caribbean Journal of Science 7: 45 - 64." type="journal article" year="1967">Maldonado Capriles and Navarro (1967)</bibRefCitation>
. According to R. R. Snelling (personal communication, 1999), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. versicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is limited to the Lesser Antilles; however several Greater Antillean species have been misidentified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[227,381,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis box="[227,381,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. versicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
